  "text": "This most complete sample of LMC SNRs allows us to better study their morphology, evolution and physical processes that are responsible for their observed emission. To get better statistical insight into the physical properties of the LMC SNRs, we reconstructed the probability density function (PDF) for diameter, flux density, spectral index and ovality. We note that the errors associated with the diameter (<2 ′′ ) and flux density (<10%) are small and not displayed in this analysis. For n independent and identically distributed (iid) measurements of a variable X(x 1 , x 2 , x 3 , ..., x n ), the PDF (f (x)) is reconstructed using the Gaussian kernel smoothing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Sheather 2004) , with the kernel function:",
